# Typography System Overview

The Intuit Design System provides typography through the `@ids-ts/typography` package, which exports React components for rendering text with the correct design tokens applied automatically.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/typography
```

```tsx
import {
  Typography,
  D1, D2, D3, D4,
  H1, H2, H3, H4, H5, H6,
  B1, B2, B3, B4,
  Bold, Demi, Medium, Regular, Thin, Heavy,
} from '@ids-ts/typography';
import '@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css';
```

Always import the CSS file alongside the component import. The CSS path is `@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css`.

## Preset Components

The package exports shorthand preset components that map to specific typography scales and render the correct semantic HTML elements automatically.

### Display Presets (D1–D4)

For large, prominent text like hero sections or marketing pages. Renders as `<span>`.

| Preset | Font Size Token | Resolved Size | Default Weight |
|--------|----------------|---------------|----------------|
| `D1` | `--font-size-display-1` | 84px | 700 (bold) |
| `D2` | `--font-size-display-2` | 72px | 700 (bold) |
| `D3` | `--font-size-display-3` | 60px | 700 (bold) |
| `D4` | `--font-size-display-4` | 48px | 700 (bold) |

```tsx
<D1>Large Display Text</D1>
<D3>Smaller Display Text</D3>
```

### Heading Presets (H1–H6)

For section headings and page titles. Renders as the corresponding `<h1>`–`<h6>` element.

| Preset | Font Size Token | Resolved Size | Default Weight |
|--------|----------------|---------------|----------------|
| `H1` | `--font-size-heading-1` | 48px | 600 (demi) |
| `H2` | `--font-size-heading-2` | 40px | 600 (demi) |
| `H3` | `--font-size-heading-3` | 34px | 600 (demi) |
| `H4` | `--font-size-heading-4` | 28px | 600 (demi) |
| `H5` | `--font-size-heading-5` | 24px | 600 (demi) |
| `H6` | `--font-size-heading-6` | 20px | 600 (demi) |

```tsx
<H1>Page Title</H1>
<H3>Section Heading</H3>
<H6>Small Heading</H6>
```

### Body Presets (B1–B4)

For paragraph and body text. Renders as `<span>`.

| Preset | Font Size Token | Resolved Size | Default Weight |
|--------|----------------|---------------|----------------|
| `B1` | `--font-size-body-1` | 20px | 400 (regular) |
| `B2` | `--font-size-body-2` | 16px | 400 (regular) |
| `B3` | `--font-size-body-3` | 14px | 400 (regular) |
| `B4` | `--font-size-body-4` | 12px | 400 (regular) |

```tsx
<B1>Large body text</B1>
<B2>Default body text (most common)</B2>
<B3>Small body text</B3>
<B4>Caption or fine print</B4>
```

### Weight Presets

For overriding font weight on any text. These render as `<span>` and are typically nested inside other presets.

| Preset | Weight Value |
|--------|-------------|
| `Thin` | 200 |
| `Regular` | 400 |
| `Medium` | 500 |
| `Demi` | 600 |
| `Bold` | 700 |
| `Heavy` | 800 |

```tsx
<B2>Normal text with <Bold>bold emphasis</Bold> inline.</B2>
```

## Typography Component Props

The base `Typography` component accepts these props:

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `variant` | `'display-1'` \| `'display-2'` \| `'display-3'` \| `'display-4'` \| `'headline-1'` \| `'headline-2'` \| `'headline-3'` \| `'headline-4'` \| `'headline-5'` \| `'headline-6'` \| `'body-1'` \| `'body-2'` \| `'body-3'` \| `'body-4'` \| `'inherit'` | `'body-2'` | Typography scale variant |
| `weight` | `'thin'` \| `'regular'` \| `'medium'` \| `'demi'` \| `'bold'` \| `'heavy'` | varies by variant | Font weight override |
| `as` | `React.ElementType` | varies by variant | Override the rendered HTML element |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | required | Text content |

All preset components (`D1`, `H1`, `B2`, etc.) accept the same props.

### Variant to HTML Element Mapping

| Variant | Default HTML Element |
|---------|---------------------|
| `display-1` through `display-4` | `<span>` |
| `headline-1` | `<h1>` |
| `headline-2` | `<h2>` |
| `headline-3` | `<h3>` |
| `headline-4` | `<h4>` |
| `headline-5` | `<h5>` |
| `headline-6` | `<h6>` |
| `body-1` through `body-4` | `<span>` |
| `inherit` | `<span>` |

## Usage Patterns

### Basic Usage with Presets (Preferred)

```tsx
import { H1, H3, B2, B3 } from '@ids-ts/typography';
import '@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css';

function MyPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      <H1>Page Title</H1>
      <H3>Section Heading</H3>
      <B2>This is the default body text size, suitable for most content.</B2>
      <B3>This is smaller body text for secondary information.</B3>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Using the Typography Component Directly

```tsx
import { Typography } from '@ids-ts/typography';
import '@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css';

<Typography variant="headline-3">Section Heading</Typography>
<Typography variant="body-2">Body paragraph text</Typography>
<Typography variant="display-1" weight="heavy">Large Display</Typography>
```

### Overriding the HTML Element

Use the `as` prop when you need a specific semantic element that differs from the default:

```tsx
<B2 as="h3" weight="demi">
  Visually styled as B2 but renders as an h3 element
</B2>

<D1 as="h1">Hero Title</D1>
```

### Inline Weight Overrides

```tsx
<H3>
  Text that has <strong>partial bolding</strong> automatically applied.
</H3>

<H3 weight="bold">
  This entire heading uses bold weight.
</H3>

<B2>
  Normal text with <Bold>bold</Bold> and <Demi>demi</Demi> inline.
</B2>
```

### Text Alignment

Typography components inherit text alignment from their parent container:

```css
.centered {
  text-align: center;
}
```

```tsx
<div className={styles.centered}>
  <H2>Centered Heading</H2>
  <B2>Centered body text</B2>
</div>
```

## Typography Design Tokens

When you need to style custom elements (not using Typography components), use these token categories together:

### Font Size Tokens

| Category | Tokens | Sizes |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Display | `--font-size-display-1` to `--font-size-display-4` | 84px, 72px, 60px, 48px |
| Heading | `--font-size-heading-1` to `--font-size-heading-6` | 48px, 40px, 34px, 28px, 24px, 20px |
| Body | `--font-size-body-1` to `--font-size-body-4` | 20px, 16px, 14px, 12px |
| Component | `--font-size-component-x-small` to `--font-size-component-x-large` | 12px, 14px, 16px, 20px, 24px |
| Action | `--font-size-action-x-small` to `--font-size-action-large` | 12px, 14px, 16px, 20px |
| Input | `--font-size-input-text`, `--font-size-input-label` | 16px, 14px |

### Font Weight Tokens

| Token | Value | Use Case |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `--font-weight-body` | 400 | Body/paragraph text |
| `--font-weight-body-semibold` | 500 | Emphasized body text |
| `--font-weight-body-bold` | 600 | Bold body text |
| `--font-weight-heading` | 600 | Heading text |
| `--font-weight-heading-bold` | 800 | Bold headings |
| `--font-weight-display` | 700 | Display text |
| `--font-weight-display-bold` | 900 | Bold display text |
| `--font-weight-component` | 400 | Component text |
| `--font-weight-component-semibold` | 500 | Emphasized component text |
| `--font-weight-component-bold` | 600 | Bold component text |

### Font Family Tokens

| Token | Use Case |
|-------|----------|
| `--font-family-body` | Body/paragraph text |
| `--font-family-heading` | Heading text |
| `--font-family-display` | Display text |
| `--font-family-component` | Component text |
| `--font-family-mega` | Marketing mega text |

All resolve to the Avenir Next forINTUIT font stack with appropriate fallbacks.

### Line Height Tokens

| Token | Value | Use Case |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `--line-height-body` | 1.5 | Body/paragraph text |
| `--line-height-heading` | 1.3 | Heading text |
| `--line-height-display` | 1.3 | Display text |
| `--line-height-component` | 1.3 | Component text |
| `--line-height-mega` | 1.2 | Marketing mega text |

## Custom Typography with Tokens

When styling text outside of Typography components, always apply all four core properties:

```css
.customHeading {
  font-size: var(--font-size-heading-3);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-heading);
  line-height: var(--line-height-heading);
  font-family: var(--font-family-heading);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  margin: 0;
}

.customBody {
  font-size: var(--font-size-body-2);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-body);
  font-family: var(--font-family-body);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.customCaption {
  font-size: var(--font-size-body-4);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-body);
  font-family: var(--font-family-body);
  color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
}
```

## Guidelines

### Prefer Typography Components Over Raw Tokens

Use `H1`, `B2`, etc. whenever possible. They handle font size, weight, line height, font family, and semantic HTML automatically. Only use raw tokens when styling elements that can't use Typography components.

### Do Not Override Typography in IDS Components

IDS components (`@ids-ts/button`, `@ids-ts/badge`, `@ids-ts/chip`, etc.) handle their own typography. Never override their font styles.

### Body vs Component Tokens

- **Body tokens** (`--font-size-body-*`, `--font-weight-body`) are for paragraph text and long-form content
- **Component tokens** (`--font-size-component-*`, `--font-weight-component`) are for text inside UI components like labels, badges, and chips
- Do not use body tokens inside atom-sized UI components; use component tokens instead

### Heading Margins

Typography heading presets do not add margins. If you need spacing between headings and body text, use spacing tokens:

```css
.sectionHeading {
  margin-bottom: var(--space-component-gap-medium);
}
```

## Common Anti-Patterns

### Incorrect: Hardcoded Typography Values

```css
/* Never hardcode values that have tokens */
.heading {
  font-size: 40px;
  font-weight: 800;
  line-height: 1.2;
  font-family: 'Arial';
}
```

### Incorrect: Incomplete Typography Properties

```css
/* Missing font-weight, line-height, and font-family */
.heading {
  font-size: var(--font-size-heading-1);
}
```

### Incorrect: Overriding IDS Component Typography

```tsx
/* Do not override IDS component styles */
<Button style={{ fontSize: '20px', fontWeight: 700 }}>
  Click Me
</Button>
```

### Incorrect: Wrong CSS Import Path

```tsx
/* Wrong */
import '@ids-ts/typography/typography.css';

/* Correct */
import '@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css';
```

## Pre-Implementation Checklist

- [ ] Typography CSS imported: `import '@ids-ts/typography/dist/main.css'`
- [ ] Using preset components (`H1`, `B2`, etc.) where possible
- [ ] Using `as` prop when semantic HTML element needs to differ from visual style
- [ ] Custom text styles use all four token properties (font-size, font-weight, line-height, font-family)
- [ ] No hardcoded typography values
- [ ] No typography overrides on IDS components
- [ ] Body tokens used for paragraph text; component tokens used for UI component text
- [ ] Text color uses `--color-text-*` tokens
- [ ] Heading elements have `margin: 0` when using custom CSS

